{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Kanban API",
    "description": "Multi-tenant Kanban backend (HTTP). Import this file into Postman (Import → File).\n\n**Setup**\n1. Set collection variables: `baseUrl` (e.g. `http://localhost:3000`), and optionally `orgId`, `boardId`, `columnId`, `cardId` from list responses. For attachment flows, optionally set `attachmentId` manually or rely on **Upload attachment** Tests (saved from `data.id`).\n2. **Register** or **Login** — the `Tests` script saves `accessToken` from the response into a collection variable.\n3. Other requests use **Bearer** auth with that token. **Memberships** — `GET /memberships/me` returns all org memberships for the JWT user; `GET /memberships/:orgId` returns your role in one org. Org scoping for other routes is inferred from path params (`orgId`, `boardId`, `cardId`, etc.) by the server’s `RolesGuard`.\n\n**OpenAPI** — Interactive docs: `{{baseUrl}}/api` (Swagger UI).\n\n**WebSockets** (not in this collection): `board` and `chat` namespaces — see project README for `joinBoard` / `joinOrg`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "orgId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "boardId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "columnId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "cardId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "attachmentId", "value": "" },
